{"id":217871140,"web_url":"https://www.kansas.com/news/nation-world/national/article217871140.html","type":"story","title":"Nurse with Choctaw Nation sent a Snapchat about ‘fat natives.’ She lost her job","publication":{"short_name":"kansas","long_name":"The Wichita Eagle"},"modified_date":"2018-09-05T21:22:52Z","published_date":"2018-09-05T21:22:28Z","authors":[{"name":"Kaitlyn Alanis","email":"kalanis@wichitaeagle.com"}],"summary":"\u003cdiv xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eJill White, a nurse who was employed by the Choctaw Nation of Oklahoma, is no longer employed after she sent a Snapcat about “fat natives” playing softball during the Indian Tribe’s Labor Day festival. \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","body":"\u003cdiv xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eWith a “fake smile,” a Choctaw Nation employee sent a Snapchat photo that would eventually cost her the nursing job she had with the Native American tribe’s medical facilities. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e“My fake smile,” the photo’s text said, according to a screenshot obtained by KXII. “Excited to go make sure a bunch of \u003ca href=\"http://www.kxii.com/content/news/Snapchat-post-about-Native-Americans-causes-controversy-492460861.html\" target=\"_blank\"\u003efat natives don’t stroke out\u003c/a\u003e playing softball. With no shoes or shirts on.” \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn the photo, the employee identified by KXII as Jill White, can be seen wearing her employee name badge. White is a registered nurse, according to her Facebook page viewed by the TV station. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhite was working at the Choctaw Nation Labor Day festival’s tribal \u003ca href=\"https://kfor.com/2018/09/04/people-are-calling-nurse-to-be-fired-after-offensive-native-american-joke/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esoftball game when she sent the Snapchat\u003c/a\u003e, KFOR reported. The post was deleted, the station reported, but it was shared on social media and led to controversial posts.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e \u003c!-- %asset:217876305% --\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eJosh Muncy, a friend of White’s and a member of the Indian Tribe, sent an email to the Choctaw Nation Chief claiming that White’s post was an “inside joke,” according to KFOR. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHe said the joke was regarding “a name he wanted to give his softball team because he said they’re overweight and Native American,” the station reported. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eBut on Wednesday, the tribe posted that the employee who sent the photo was “no longer employed” with Choctaw Nation of Oklahoma. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e“Disparaging words, even when joking, are never acceptable,” the post said. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003c!-- %asset:217877190% --\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe post confirmed that the employee had made “disparaging comments on social media while serving as a representative of the Choctaw Nation at the annual Choctaw Nation Labor Day Festival.” \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eOne of White’s friends told News9 that \u003ca href=\"http://www.news9.com/story/39025042/controversial-social-media-post-targeting-native-americans-leads-to-death-threats\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eWhite was fired on Tuesday\u003c/a\u003e, the station reported. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e“We will continue to share our values and beliefs of faith, family and culture,” Choctaw Nation of Oklahoma posted. “Never focusing on hatred, always standing united in a spirit of love.” \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pg/choctawnationofoklahoma/about/?ref=page_internal\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eThe Choctaw Nation\u003c/a\u003e is the third largest federally recognized tribe in the U.S., according to its Facebook page. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e \u003c!-- %asset:213617129% --\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","seo":{"keywords":"nurse, job, indian, tribe, native american, snapchat, Choctaw Nation, Oklahoma"},"_links":{"self":{"href":"/newsapi/v1/stories/217871140?publication=kansas"},"home_section":{"href":"/newsapi/v1/sections/3289","asset":{"id":3289,"name":"National","taxonomy":"News|National|||","web_url":"https://www.kansas.com/news/nation-world/national/","unique_name":"national","_links":{"self":{"href":"/newsapi/v1/sections/3289"}}}},"home_publication":{"href":"/newsapi/v1/publications/kansas"},"lead_media":{"href":"/newsapi/v1/images/217877385?publication=kansas","asset":{"id":217877385,"file_url":"https://www.kansas.com/latest-news/30mkj6/picture217877385/alternates/FREE_1140/Choctaw%20Nation.JPG","caption":"A nurse is no longer employed with Choctaw Nation of Oklahoma after she sent a Snapchat about “fat natives” playing softball during the Native American tribe’s Labor Day festival.","credit":"KFOR video","photographer":"Screen capture","thumbnail":"https://www.kansas.com/latest-news/30mkj6/picture217877385/alternates/FREE_1140/Choctaw%20Nation.JPG","publication":{"id":0,"long_name":"The Wichita Eagle","short_name":"kansas","time_zone":"","web_url":"","analytics":{"market_code":"","site_file":""},"_links":{"self":{"href":""}}},"modified_date":"2018-09-05T21:02:12Z","published_date":"2018-09-05T20:52:27Z"}},"related":[{"href":"/newsapi/v1/images/217877385?publication=kansas","asset":{"id":217877385,"file_url":"https://www.kansas.com/latest-news/30mkj6/picture217877385/alternates/FREE_1140/Choctaw%20Nation.JPG","caption":"A nurse is no longer employed with Choctaw Nation of Oklahoma after she sent a Snapchat about “fat natives” playing softball during the Native American tribe’s Labor Day festival.","credit":"KFOR video","photographer":"Screen capture","thumbnail":"https://www.kansas.com/latest-news/30mkj6/picture217877385/alternates/FREE_1140/Choctaw%20Nation.JPG","publication":{"id":0,"long_name":"The Wichita Eagle","short_name":"kansas","time_zone":"","web_url":"","analytics":{"market_code":"","site_file":""},"_links":{"self":{"href":""}}},"modified_date":"2018-09-05T21:02:12Z","publishe